name: r-pagedown
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.18" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-pagedown
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/pagedown_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/pagedown/pagedown_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 3fcfd6de2a4e35635dbada06813d94947066994d99631e9d442d31c61ac55ed3

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-bookdown >=0.8
    - r-htmltools
    - r-httpuv
    - r-jsonlite
    - r-later >=1.0.0
    - r-processx
    - r-rmarkdown >=2.8
    - r-servr >=0.23
    - r-websocket
    - r-xfun
    - pandoc >=2.2.3
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-bookdown >=0.8
    - r-htmltools
    - r-httpuv
    - r-jsonlite
    - r-later >=1.0.0
    - r-processx
    - r-rmarkdown >=2.8
    - r-servr >=0.23
    - r-websocket
    - r-xfun
    - pandoc >=2.2.3

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('pagedown')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('pagedown')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/rstudio/pagedown
  license: MIT
  summary: Use the paged media properties in CSS and the JavaScript library 'paged.js' to split the content of an HTML document into discrete pages. Each page can have its page size, page numbers, margin boxes, and running headers, etc. Applications of this package include books, letters, reports, papers, business cards,
    resumes, and posters.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
